      "message": "AI based review:\n\n-----\n\n#### 1. The Vulnerability\n\nThe boundary check relies on the minimum root tuple size of $5$ bytes before invoking `bejInitSFLVStruct`:\n\n```c\nif (streamLen \u003c bejMinRootSflvSize)\n{\n    fprintf(stderr, \"Stream too short for a BEJ root tuple (%u \u003c %u)\\n\",\n    streamLen, bejMinRootSflvSize);\n    return bejErrorInvalidSize;\n}\nif (!bejInitSFLVStruct(\u0026params))\n{\n    return bejErrorInvalidSize;\n}\n```\n\nWhile this check ensures that:\n`streamLen \u003e\u003d 5`\nit does not guarantee that the parsed length fields within the root SFLV conform to the actual buffer constraints.\n\n#### 2. Exploit Scenario\n\nIf a device sends a 5-byte buffer (satisfying the check) where the first byte is set to `0xFF`:\n1. `bejInitSFLVStruct` delegates parsing of the sequence number to `bejGetNnint(params-\u003estate.encodedSubStream)`.\n2. `bejGetNnint` extracts the size byte `0xFF` ($255$) as the nnint length:\n   ```c\n   const uint8_t size \u003d *nnint;\n   ```\n3. `bejGetUnsignedInteger` is called with a size parameter of $255$:\n   ```c\n   return bejGetUnsignedInteger(nnint + sizeof(uint8_t), size);\n   ```\n4. `bejGetUnsignedInteger` loops $255$ times reading `bytes + i`, resulting in an out-of-bounds heap read of $250$ bytes past the allocation limit:\n   ```c\n   for (uint8_t i \u003d 0; i \u003c numOfBytes; ++i) {\n       num |\u003d (uint64_t)(*(bytes + i)) \u003c\u003c (i * 8);\n   }\n   ```\n\nThis can lead to a core dump (Denial of Service) or information disclosure.\n\n#### 3. Recommended Fix\n\nTo make `bejInitSFLVStruct` and `bejGetNnint` secure:\n1. **Pass Buffer Constraints:** `bejInitSFLVStruct` must be updated to take a remaining stream size constraint parameter.\n2. **Size Validation Check:** Before invoking `bejGetNnint`, validate that the size byte does not exceed the remaining buffer length:\n   ```c\n   if (remainingBytes \u003c 1 || *nnint + 1 \u003e remainingBytes)\n   {\n       return bejErrorInvalidSize;\n   }\n   ```",
